{"_id":"InDSKbnEwiwBQUeq","name":"Flail","content":"<p>Weapons of this type are able to strike unpredictably. These weapons cannot be parried or countered, but cannot be used to parry or counter attack either. If an attacker with this weapon and a defender blocking with a shield both pass their respective tests, and the attacker’s degrees of success exceed those of the defender, then the defender does not block the attack as they normally would and the attack is resolved as if the attacker had won. If a character critically fails an attack with a flail they hit themselves. </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qtm3mdw5kon","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Qualities#/CF_SEP/Weapon Qualities","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"J1fYlZ5DQd3of7iS","name":"Arcane","content":"<p>Weapons with this quality are treated as having the Focus quality, as well as doubling the amount of charges of any cast enchantment placed upon it.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qtm3mdw5kon","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Qualities#/CF_SEP/Weapon Qualities","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Damage & Hit Locations","content":"<p>Damage represents the ability of an attack to harm a character. Attacks against a character always strike a particular hit location (determined by the 1s digit of the attack roll, or a d10 counting 10 as 0), and the damage of that attack is reduced by the Armor Rating (AR) of that hit location. The characters Hit Points (HP) are then reduced by the remaining amount.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<table style=\"width:99.1549%\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:32.4902%\"><strong>                           Result</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:66.7995%\"><strong>                                                                  Location Hit</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:32.4902%\">1-5</td>\n<td style=\"width:66.7995%\">Body</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:32.4902%\">6</td>\n<td style=\"width:66.7995%\">Right Leg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:32.4902%\">7</td>\n<td style=\"width:66.7995%\">Left Leg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:32.4902%\">8</td>\n<td style=\"width:66.7995%\">Right Arm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:32.4902%\">9</td>\n<td style=\"width:66.7995%\">Left Arm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:32.4902%\">0</td>\n<td style=\"width:66.7995%\">Head</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Damage Types</strong></p>\n<p>The above rules hold true for all physical attacks and physical armor. However, some attacks and effects can deal other types of damage that can only be resisted with certain types of armor. Broadly, damage can be divided into two overall types</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Physical Damage</strong></p>\n<p>Physical damage represents physical cuts, jabs, and blows that harm a character through force of impact or blood loss (or both). All normal weapons deal physical damage, and physical damage is reduced by normal AR.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Magic Damage</strong></p>\n<p>Magic damage represents damage dealt by magical or elemental forces, such as burns from a fire ball spell. Poison is included in this category, though it is not always magical. There are sub-types of magic damage, each reduced by a corresponding armor type (and also reduced by generic magic AR).</p>\n<p> </p>\n<table style=\"width:99.1477%\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:33.4223%\"><strong>                          Sub-Type</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:65.8614%\"><strong>                                                            Armour Type</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:33.4223%\">(any)</td>\n<td style=\"width:65.8614%\">Magic AR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:33.4223%\">Fire</td>\n<td style=\"width:65.8614%\">Fire AR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:33.4223%\">Frost</td>\n<td style=\"width:65.8614%\">Frost AR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:33.4223%\">Shock</td>\n<td style=\"width:65.8614%\">Shock AR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:33.4223%\">Poison</td>\n<td style=\"width:65.8614%\">Poison Ar</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3ne3rdpl9xs","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Combat","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"J4R9A3uc40YoI6JR"}
{"name":"Dazed","content":"<p>The character gains one less action point at the beginning of their turn, to a minimum of one.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_hw0xe1g9xxt","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Conditions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JRXHJW251nVbRubN"}
{"name":"Melee Combat","content":"<p>Melee combat is any combat that happens within several meters, where participants fight either with wielded or natural weapons. The melee weapons a character can use are listed as part of their Combat Style skills.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Melee Combat Circumstance Modifiers</strong></p>\n<p>Like all tests, tests made in melee combat should always be subject to difficulty based on the environment or circumstances in which the combat is happening. Disadvantageous circumstances can be rated in a simple scale by the GM, and should not usually be worse than -30. The table below provides the scale and some examples.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<table style=\"width:99.1549%;height:68px\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"width:44.0948%;height:17px\"><strong>                                 Modifier</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:55.1949%;height:17px\"><strong>                                 Common Examples</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"width:44.0948%;height:17px\">Minor Disadvantage (-10)</td>\n<td style=\"width:55.1949%;height:17px\">Fighting in poor visibility</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"width:44.0948%;height:17px\">Disadvantage (-20)</td>\n<td style=\"width:55.1949%;height:17px\">Fighting from lower ground or prone</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height:17px\">\n<td style=\"width:44.0948%;height:17px\">Major Disadvantage (-30)</td>\n<td style=\"width:55.1949%;height:17px\">Fighting blind</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_6jigz5c9dio","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Combat#/CF_SEP/Attacking & Defending","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JWVX9cJE1TChuMtT"}
