{"_id":"MDxdxWBJw1XoPHb2","name":"Wavy Blade","content":"<p>+5 to Counterattack, -5 to Parry. Increases bonus to +10 against polearms.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qtm3mdw5kon","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Qualities#/CF_SEP/Weapon Qualities","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Grappling","content":"<p>In place of making a normal attack a character can choose to attempt to grapple their opponent. This requires a Combat Style test (the style must include unarmed combat) opposed against either a Combat Style (with unarmed), Athletics, or Evade test. On success, the target gains the restrained condition. The target may attempt to escape by using the resist action. On success they break free.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>Characters suffer a -30 penalty when attempting to grapple characters of larger size than them, and cannot grapple characters of two or more sizes larger. While they have an opponent restrained, the character may not move but may take the following actions (each is a primary action that costs 1 AP):</p>\n<p>• Takedown: The character may render their victim, and themself, prone. They suffers no prone penalties in relation to any tests made against they target.</p>\n<p>• Move: The character may move themself and their victim a number of meters up to their Strength bonus in any direction.</p>\n<p>• Attack: The character may make a normal attack against their restrained victim, who cannot defend themself. They must use a weapon with a 1m range or less. If the target is both prone and restrained, and the character is armed, this can be a coup de grâce. If the character is unarmed, then they can choose to instead cause the target to lose Strength Bonus Stamina points.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_3ne3rdpl9xs","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Combat","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"MIcUO788QJuXtfKW"}
{"name":"Jumping","content":"<p>A character may also make an Acrobatics test to jump over or up to an obstacle, either horizontally or vertically. This can represent either completely clearing the obstacle, or just jumping high enough to grab it with both hands, depending on what the GM feels is appropriate. If the character does not spend several seconds running or otherwise preparing (approximately a round) before the jump then they suffer a -10 penalty to the test.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>When jumping vertically, each meter they wish to jump beyond the first imposes a -20 penalty on the test. When jumping horizontally, each meter they wish to jump beyond the first imposes a -10 penalty on the test. Critical Failure results in the character tumbling to the ground.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_k65789wa1kl","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Movement","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"N1tWlfQOwD2hHE1n"}
{"_id":"NVsmi1emFa7DEUOE","name":"Snare","content":"<p>This weapon can be used to perform the Bash and Trip Special Actions at range. Doing so always uses the attacker’s Combat Style skill against the defenders Athletics or Evade skill, and ignores the range limitation of 2 meters.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qtm3mdw5kon","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Qualities#/CF_SEP/Weapon Qualities","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Immobilized","content":"<p>Immobilized characters cannot move. They may still attack and take other actions, and can defend themselves.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_hw0xe1g9xxt","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Conditions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Nu1nNClhl73nLXW6"}
{"name":"Bleeding","content":"<p>At the end of the character’s next turn, they immediately take X damage that bypasses all armor and resistances. All Bleeding (X) conditions then expire.</p>\n<p>If a character is affected by multiple Bleeding (X) effects in one round, only use the highest one.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_hw0xe1g9xxt","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Conditions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"Of5mt1fvj37x1c0t"}
{"_id":"Q21irFmSziioerAo","name":"Shield Splitter","content":"<p>Attacks from this weapon halve the BR of shields used to block them (round up).</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qtm3mdw5kon","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Qualities#/CF_SEP/Weapon Qualities","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Q8ED7VzyqBKpfxEo","name":"Impaling","content":"<p>If this weapon is used to make an attack of opportunity against a character who is approaching the wielder, and that attack causes the target to lose HP, the target does not advance and instead halts their movement for the turn. </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qtm3mdw5kon","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Qualities#/CF_SEP/Weapon Qualities","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"Q9KA3kwbKdsLbovZ","name":"Electrifying","content":"<p><span style=\"color:#191813\">The character can, as a free action, change the composition of his Shehai. When he does this, hits with the Shehai deal shock damage.</span></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_sn2172bakil","color":"#000000"}}}
{"_id":"QO7k5VGWh1rRYpIM","name":"Serrated Edge","content":"<p>Bleed effect for Serrated quality (X*2), subtract X from Slashing or Splitting quality to a min. of 0.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_qtm3mdw5kon","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Qualities#/CF_SEP/Weapon Qualities","color":"#000000"}}}
{"name":"Ridged Shoulder Guard","content":"<p>Can only be installed on Full armour Chest with 4 AR+. Adds +1 ENC. Whenever the Head hit-location is struck, roll 1D10. On a result of 9 or 10, the blow is deflected to the body instead of the head.</p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"eeXhsDlbzUBZOXZT":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u0ce34u73r","path":"References#/CF_SEP/Qualities#/CF_SEP/Armour Qualities","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"QfadUf70SsFJMgKi"}
